  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Took a quick glance on our validator client and I think it needs some clean up to align to the latest 0.7 spec. Couple items I see are out of date and can be improved on:\r\n\r\n1. Combine `BeaconClient` and `ValidatorClient` the separations of the two dont make sense and it's confusing. Other than `ProposerClient` and `AttesterClient`, we really just need 1 actor to query information on beacon chain like assignments\r\n2. Revisit validator status usage, this may be outdated\r\n3. Revisit rewards and penalties reporting, this may be outdated\r\n",
